# M3 Memory: Scheduled Tasks Template
# Replace [M3_MEMORY_ROOT] with your absolute project path (e.g., /path/to/your/m3-memory)
#
# Entrypoints self-log via bin/_task_runtime.py — each takes a --log-file arg
# instead of relying on a shell `>>` redirect, and refuses to run a second
# concurrent instance (logs a quiet "duplicate process" line and exits 0).
#
# The cognitive loop is NOT a cron entry — it is a long-running daemon
# installed as a launchd agent (macOS) / systemd --user unit (Linux) by
# bin/install_schedules.py.
#
# The >>> m3-managed >>> / <<< m3-managed <<< sentinels below delimit the block
# the installer manages. On reinstall it removes ONLY the lines between them,
# never lines merely mentioning the install path — do not edit this block by hand.

# >>> m3-managed (do not edit this block) >>>
# Weekly auditor (Fridays 4pm)
0 16 * * 5 [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/.venv/bin/python3 [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/bin/weekly_auditor.py --log-file [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/logs/auditor.log

# Hourly sync: SQLite <-> PostgreSQL (pve-database-host)
# pg_sync.sh delegates to sync_all.py
0 * * * * [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/bin/pg_sync.sh >> [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/logs/sync_all.log 2>&1

# Daily Memory Maintenance (3:00 AM) - Decay scores, prune orphans
0 3 * * * [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/.venv/bin/python3 [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/bin/memory_maintenance.py --log-file [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/logs/maintenance.log

# Monthly Automated Secret Rotation (1st of every month at 2:00 AM)
0 2 1 * * [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/.venv/bin/python3 [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/bin/secret_rotator.py --log-file [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/logs/secret_rotator.log

# Every 30 minutes: Embed un-embedded chat_log rows using the local embedding server
*/30 * * * * [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/.venv/bin/python3 [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/bin/chatlog_embed_sweeper.py --batch 256 --max-per-run 10000 --log-file [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/logs/chatlog_embed_sweep.log

# Every 15 minutes: Drain observation_queue (extract user-facts from chatlog conversations)
*/15 * * * * [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/.venv/bin/python3 [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/bin/m3_enrich.py --drain-queue --drain-batch 200 --profile enrich_local_qwen --log-file [M3_MEMORY_ROOT]/logs/observation_drain.log
# <<< m3-managed <<<

# NOTE: belief consolidation (knowledge-maintenance Phase 4) is NOT a cron entry.
# It runs as a governor-gated, event-driven pass inside the cognitive-loop daemon
# (run_consolidate_pass in bin/m3_cognitive_loop.py) so it yields to an active
# user / loaded host like every other expensive pass, and only fires when an aged
# group actually exceeds the threshold. bin/consolidate_beliefs.py remains for
# manual/CLI runs. Real writes still require M3_CONSOLIDATION_AUTO=1.
